HEADWORD: Catchfly
<hw>Catch"fly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
plant with the joints of the stem, and sometimes other parts, covered
with a viscid secretion to which small insects adhere. The species of
<gen>Silene</gen> are examples of the catchfly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

